                                   CROCODILE
                                  -----------


Only one great reptile has survived the age of the dinosaur - the crocodile. Ancient they may be, but they are still the most successful of freshwater hunters. Only now, by exploring their complete world, above and below water, by day and night, can we fully appreciate just how sophisticated they are. In survival terms, the crocodile has every reason to smile. 


David Attenborough has launched his own video collection, featuring the finest BBC Wildlife Specials, as well as memorable films from The Natural World and Wildlife on One series. Each video is individually introduced and narrated by David Attenborough.
